<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About - Barangay Directory</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bulma@0.9.4/css/bulma.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="box">
        <h1 class="title is-1">üèòÔ∏è Barangay Officials Directory</h1>
        <p class="subtitle is-3">Digital Record Management System</p>
        
        <hr>

        <div class="content">
          <h2 class="title is-3">About This System</h2>
          <p class="is-size-5">
            This web application serves as a digital directory for Barangay San Jose officials. 
            It provides an easy way to view contact information and manage records of elected 
            and appointed barangay officials.
          </p>

          <h3 class="title is-4">üéØ Features</h3>
          <div class="columns">
            <div class="column">
              <div class="box has-background-primary-light">
                <h4 class="subtitle is-5">‚úÖ View Officials</h4>
                <p>Browse all registered barangay officials with their complete information including position, contact details, and address.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <div class="box has-background-info-light">
                <h4 class="subtitle is-5">‚ûï Add Officials</h4>
                <p>Register new barangay officials through an easy-to-use form with validation to ensure data accuracy.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <div class="box has-background-success-light">
                <h4 class="subtitle is-5">üìä Statistics</h4>
                <p>View summary statistics showing the distribution of officials by position and role.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="title is-4">üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used</h3>
          <div class="columns">
            <div class="column">
              <strong>Backend:</strong>
              <ul>
                <li>Node.js - JavaScript runtime</li>
                <li>Express.js - Web framework</li>
                <li>File System (fs) - JSON data storage</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <strong>Frontend:</strong>
              <ul>
                <li>EJS - Template engine</li>
                <li>Bulma CSS - UI framework</li>
                <li>HTML5 - Form validation</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <strong>Data:</strong>
              <ul>
                <li>JSON Files - Data persistence</li>
                <li>Structured records</li>
                <li>File-based storage</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="title is-4">üìã Barangay Positions</h3>
          <table class="table is-fullwidth is-striped">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Position</th>
                <th>Role</th>
                <th>Term</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Barangay Captain</strong></td>
                <td>Head of the barangay, presides over meetings</td>
                <td>3 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Barangay Kagawad</strong></td>
                <td>Council member, assists in governance</td>
                <td>3 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>SK Chairperson</strong></td>
                <td>Leads Sangguniang Kabataan (youth council)</td>
                <td>3 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Barangay Secretary</strong></td>
                <td>Maintains records and documents</td>
                <td>Appointed</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Barangay Treasurer</strong></td>
                <td>Manages barangay funds</td>
                <td>Appointed</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3 class="title is-4">üéì Learning Objectives</h3>
          <p>This mini-project demonstrates:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>CRUD Operations</strong> - Create (Add) and Read (View) functionality</li>
            <li><strong>Form Handling</strong> - HTML forms with validation and POST requests</li>
            <li><strong>JSON Data Management</strong> - Reading and writing structured data</li>
            <li><strong>EJS Templates</strong> - Dynamic HTML generation with loops and conditionals</li>
            <li><strong>Bulma CSS</strong> - Responsive design and modern UI components</li>
            <li><strong>Philippine Context</strong> - Real-world barangay governance system</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="notification is-warning is-light mt-5">
            <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Note:</strong> This is a learning project using JSON files for data storage. 
            In a production environment, a proper database (like SQLite or PostgreSQL) would be used 
            for better performance, security, and scalability.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="buttons mt-5">
            <a href="/" class="button is-primary is-medium">
              <strong>View Officials Directory</strong>
            </a>
            <a href="/add" class="button is-info is-medium">
              <strong>Add New Official</strong>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
